# MIDI music generator

Using markov chains to reorder notes in midi music files, creating new melodies.

## Usage

`bin/Popkadurak -f <source file> -p <pattern files> -d <dearch depth>`

where 
- `source file` - basic melody and rythm structure (midi file)
- `pattern files` - comma separated list of midi files to create markov chain
- `search depth` - markov chain search depth (less depth - more random melody)

### Example
`bin/Popkadurak -f my_melody.mid -p melody1.mid,melody2.mid,melody3.mid -d 15`

## Build from source

`make` - requires `cabal`


